Visu is a videoconferencing software mainly aimed at foreign language
courses. It features recording sessions and annotating them either
live or afterwards, to enable the production of summaries.

Visu is a free software subjected to a double license. You can
redistribute it and/or modify since you respect the terms of either
(at least one of):
- the GNU Lesser General Public License as published by the Free Software Foundation;
  either version 3 of the License, or any later version.
- the CeCILL-C as published by CeCILL; either version 2 of the License, or any later version.

It consists in a red5 server webapplication (using a MySQL database)
accessed through a flex-based frontend.

* Project organisation

The project is divided in several FlashBuilder sub-projects

** VisuFramework
A library with our Visu related components

** VisuApplication
The Visu Application itself

** HomeModule

** ProfilModule

** TutoratModule
A module for tutors during a live session.

** RetrospectionModule
A module allowing the review of a recorded session. The user can watch
a previous session, select some fragments, and add notes for the
student to make the bilan.

** BilanModule
A module for bilan management.

** UserModule
A module for user management.

** SessionModule
A module for session management.
